reviewText: I gave this a five star ratting because it was sold at a pretty good price, it was shipped and it arrived to me on time, and it was brand new- like amazon said it would be.
Title: Bleach Uncut 11

reviewText: What I find annoying: Box set 10 ends with Ichigo standing on a broken tower with Orihime holding hands, telling her let's go everyone's waiting. So how did everyone get together, Chad and Rukia were injured and could barely move. How did they leave without the spell and power to do so? Why did the battle suddenly stop with so many enemies just standing around? Suddenly Box set 11 puts us back in school everyone healed and happy and no explanation on how that came about. A princess is introduced and fighting begins again. I know Bleach is a slice and dice fighting  story line, but I actually like the comedy and a story line where they are not slicing each other up constantly. These vids are cut and edited things are blurred out or changed, so we are not getting the original version, which is greatly annoying. The price for not getting the whole arc any arc actually (only 3 disks), is now way up and that is a royal pain.What I like: Attractive/interesting characters you want to see prevail and when they are not constantly slicing and dicing,  interesting story lines. Although saving females from bad guys has been 3 (different females) arcs now is getting tiring. Love Bleach ?(I do) get the set, be prepared to pay too much, if you're into slicing and dicing only what the hell is wrong with you?
Title: Bleach Uncut 11

reviewText: To start off I will admit that this season is not as good as the main Aizen/Espada Arc. However, this is only because the main story line of Bleach is so epic. This season revolves around a princess from the soul society that Ichigo has to protect from evil ninjas. At the same time the 3rd Squad's captain is replaced by a strange new Soul Reaper. I won't delve into the story to much but it really isn't bad. There is a lot of action and I personally enjoyed the head Ninja. It isn't the best season of Bleach but I liked it better than the Bount Arc. It is worth taking the time to watch and it should hold you over until they get back to the main arc, which will hopefully come out on dvd in June.
summary: Not the best but still enjoyable
Title: Bleach Uncut 11

reviewText: Again Bleach belches and out comes some more filler right in the middle of the good stuff. This time it's not too bad. I would definitely prefer it if they would stop this bad habit of wasting time. Even though they do this all time, the filler in this box set is relatively entertaining. A princess from the soul society is being forced out of her home by her Regent. He is using her clans weapon mastery to stage a takeover. He needs to kill princess Rurichiyo in order to do this. Ichigo and Rukia are determined to put and end to this revolt.I can see some people not liking this bit. It does come right in the middle of something very important, but we all know Bleach does this crap to us pretty often. I've just accepted it and try to enjoy it for what it is. This story arc by itself is better than a lot of entire anime series out there today. Give it a chance. You may enjoy it. The next volume of Bleach is pretty good and it begins at the end of this one.
Title: Bleach Uncut 11

reviewText: Love Bleach no matter what! Some of the fillers are annoying but this was one of the better episodes. Tired of getting ripped off though on the disk sets.
Title: Bleach Uncut 11

reviewText: Bleach Uncut Box Set 11; A continuation in the series and a wonderful addition to my sons Bleach video library.  I just wish they would release the seasons a little more timely
Title: Bleach Uncut 11

reviewText: When i first bought this set i was expecting to see what happens after the battle of Ichigo and Grimmjow but oddly enough the episode started with a different story line. Its about a rich girl Rurichiyo that comes in the world of the living with her two bodyguards and are being chased by a group of assassins. Now Ichigo and Rukia have to protect this girl.The first 2 discs are just plain talk and the background of Rurichiyo but Bleach shines on episode 175 and disc 4 where Uryu, Chad, Ichigo and Rukia are challenged by the group of assassins that are after the noble girl. Fights are pretty good with lots of action.So if you are a true fan of Bleach you won't miss this set. It's not on the same level as the Arrancar Arc but it's still BLEACH!
summary: Mixed Feelings but It's still BLEACH!
Title: Bleach Uncut 11

reviewText: Love this series but this was so odd.  The story line went to a side story all of a sudden rather annoyed at the sudden stop and change of story line.  I mean really it changed without finishing the last story line.  Apparently the story with get back to it later.  Ok that just stupid.
Title: Bleach Uncut 11
